@body
There are several mailing lists associated with GNU GLOBAL: 

<h3>Bug report Mailing list</h3>

If you think you have found a bug or a suggestion for improvements in GLOBAL,
then please send a mail to
<a href="mailto:bug-global@gnu.org">&lt;bug-global@gnu.org&gt;</a>.
<p>
This list distributes, to the active maintainers of GLOBAL,
bug reports and fixes for, and suggestions for improvements in GLOBAL.
This list is also for user discussion.
<p>
To subscribe this list, please visit
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/bug-global>
http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/bug-global</a>.
<br>
See also <a href="http://www.gnu.org/prep/mailinglists.html#General Information about bug-* lists and reporting program bugs">
General Information about bug-* lists and reporting program bugs</a>.
<br>
To see the collection of prior postings to the list, visit the
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/bug-global/>Bug-global Archives</a>. 

<h3>Help Mailing list</h3>

If you need help about GLOBAL, then please send a mail to
<a href="mailto:help-global@gnu.org">&lt;help-global@gnu.org&gt;</a>.
<p>
This list is the place for authors, users and installers of GLOBAL
to ask for help.
<p>
Please obey the following manners:
<ul>
<li>Before sending a mail, please read 'FAQ' and tutorial(doc/global.texi) in the GLOBAL package.
<li>Don't send bug reports or suggestions to this list; mail them to bug-global@gnu.org instead.
<li>Don't send private mails to the person who answered your questions.
<li>Don't send HTML mail.
<li>Please describe the fact of problem <strong>CONCRETELY</strong>.
</ul>
To subscribe this list, please visit
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/help-global>
http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/help-global</a>.
<br>
See also <a href="http://www.gnu.org/prep/mailinglists.html#General Information about help-* lists">
General Information about help-* lists</a>.
<br>
To see the collection of prior postings to the list, visit the
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/help-global/>Help-global Archives</a>. 

<h3>Announcements Mailing list</h3>

This list distributes announcements and progress reports on GLOBAL.
<p>
To subscribe this list, please visit
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/info-global>
http://mail.gnu.org/mailman/listinfo/info-global</a>.
<br>
See also <a href="http://www.gnu.org/prep/mailinglists.html#General Information about info-* lists">
General Information about info-* lists</a>.
<br>
To see the collection of prior postings to the list, visit the
<a href=http://mail.gnu.org/pipermail/info-global/>Info-global Archives</a>. 
